org.cruk.genologics.api.jaxb

Class KnownNamespacePrefixMatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sun.xml.bind.marshaller.NamespacePrefixMapper
      • org.cruk.genologics.api.jaxb.KnownNamespacePrefixMatcher

  • public class KnownNamespacePrefixMatcher
extends com.sun.xml.bind.marshaller.NamespacePrefixMapper
    Implementation of the internal Sun JAXB NamespacePrefixMapper to make sure the XML documents created from JAXB have user friendly name spaces in their headers.

      • getPreferredPrefix

        public String getPreferredPrefix(String namespaceUri,
                                 String suggestion,
                                 boolean requirePrefix)
        Returns a preferred prefix for the given name space URI. This overridden method checks to see if the given name space URI is one that is known to this class. If it is, the "nice" tag is returned. If not, the suggestion is returned.
        Specified by:
        getPreferredPrefix in class com.sun.xml.bind.marshaller.NamespacePrefixMapper
        Parameters:
        namespaceUri - The name space URI for which the prefix needs to be found.
        suggestion - The suggested tag for the name space URI.
        requirePrefix - Whether a non-empty name space is required (i.e. not the default name space).
        Returns:
        The "nice" tag for the name space URI, or the suggested one if the URI is not recognised.
